PN,33806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F338A1781887673
OL,3,CJo Cox told friends 'let him hurt me'
OL,4,Cas they tried to stop killer
OL,6,FMair, who was 53 at the time, was
OL,7,Fheard shouting "Britain first" during
OL,8,Fthe incident, which happened days
OL,9,Fbefore the Brexit vote.
OL,11,FHe also attacked 78-year-old passerby
OL,12,FBernard Kenny, who tried to stop him.
OL,13,FPolice later found Nazi-related
OL,14,Fmaterial at Mair's home.
OL,16,FA court heard he was motivated by hate
OL,17,Fand his crimes were "nothing less than
OL,18,Facts of terrorism".
OL,20,FHe was given a whole-life prison
OL,21,Fsentence.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G6/10
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,339,330,260,120,000,100
PN,33807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F338A1781887673
OL,3,CJo Cox told friends 'let him hurt me'
OL,4,Cas they tried to stop killer
OL,6,FMs Aswat, a Muslim, said: "I think
OL,7,Fwhat's clear on that day was (Jo Cox)
OL,8,Fwas his target. I probably represented
OL,9,Feverything he hated, but she was
OL,10,Fabsolutely his target on that day."
OL,12,FMs Aswat and Ms Major described Mrs
OL,13,FCox as a "ball of energy" and "full of
OL,14,Flife, joy and purpose".
OL,16,FThey said her ethos was at odds with
OL,17,Fthat espoused by Mair.
OL,26,@oD@^pmoD@epn
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G7/10
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,339,330,260,120,000,100
PN,33808
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F338A1781887673
OL,3,CJo Cox told friends 'let him hurt me'
OL,4,Cas they tried to stop killer
OL,6,FMs Major said: "She was born and
OL,7,Fbrought up here. She went to
OL,8,FHeckmondwike Grammar School. She lived
OL,9,Fin Heckmondwike and she just loved the
OL,10,Fwhole ethos of this kind of area, and
OL,11,Fit's diversity.
OL,13,F"Her idea was we have got more in
OL,14,Fcommon than that which divides us, and
OL,15,Fthat was her mantra that she lived by:
OL,16,Fthat everyone should be able to come
OL,17,Ftogether, there should be no
OL,18,Fdivisions, and racism, and sexism, and
OL,19,Fmisogyny should all be things of the
OL,20,Fpast."
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G8/10
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,339,330,260,120,000,100
PN,33809
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F338A1781887673
OL,3,CJo Cox told friends 'let him hurt me'
OL,4,Cas they tried to stop killer
OL,6,FMs Aswat said ongoing divisions in
OL,7,Fsociety suggested there had been
OL,8,Flimited "progress" since Mrs Cox's
OL,9,Fmurder.
OL,11,FShe said: "I think we perhaps skipped
OL,12,Fa big step - perhaps we should have
OL,13,Fstopped the clock and paused and
OL,14,Freflected and really digested what had
OL,15,Fhappened and the gravity of it, and
OL,16,Fperhaps taken some learnings from that.
OL,18,F"Today I look back and think, maybe if
OL,19,Fwe'd done that, we wouldn't be in the
OL,20,Fspace that we are today."
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G9/10
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
